   control process. In this study, spatial odor emissions and environmental
   impacts were investigated based on a large-scale working waste transfer
   station (LSWTS) using waste container system, and a comprehensive odor
   characterization method was developed and applied in terms of the odor
   concentration (OC), theory odor concentration (TOC), total chemical
   concentration (TCC), and electric nose (EN). The detected odor
   concentration ranged from 14 to 28 (dimensionless), and MSW container
   showed the highest OC value of 28, EN of 78, and TCC of 35 (ppm) due to
