   range: 83-98\% HRmax; day 2, 87 +/- 10\% HRmax, range: 73-97\% HRmax) HR
   were similar between days.
   Conclusion: This case report demonstrates elevations in thermal strain
   over consecutive work shifts despite decreases in work effort in
   electrical utilities workers during regular work in the heat.}},
