Number = {{5}},
Pages = {{1536-1546}},
Month = {{SEP-OCT}},
Abstract = {{As a clean and renewable energy source, wind energy has been
   increasingly gaining global attention. Wind speed forecasting is of
   great significance for wind energy domain: planning and design of wind
   farms, wind farm operation control, wind power prediction, power grid
   operation scheduling, and more. Many wind speed forecasting algorithms
   have been proposed to improve forecast accuracy. In terms of such
   factors, in this article, a novel hybrid wind speed forecasting method
   was proposed based on Kalman filter and Generalized regression neural
   network as well as the idea of filtering error threshold in data
   preprocessing. The proposed models can implement long-term wind speed
   forecasting with higher precision and reliability compared with single
