Year = {{2004}},
Volume = {{64}},
Number = {{5}},
Pages = {{207-216}},
Month = {{MAY}},
Abstract = {{Endotoxins are part of the outer membrane of gram-negative bacteria.
   They are ubiquitous components of bioaerosols and occur at several work
   places. With respect to occupational exposure, airborne endotoxins are
   of main interest. Especially since in 1999 the Ordinance on safety and
   health protection related to work involving biological agents
   (Biostoffverordnung) became effective, threshold limit values are widely
   discussed. Up to now endotoxin values are measured with non standardized
   methods. Received endotoxin values are not comparable between different
   workplaces and vary widely from one industry sector to another.
   Therefore, in Germany no threshold limit value for endotoxin is
   currently favoured. Methods for sampling and endotoxin determination
   have to be validated, optimized and standardized first. In consequence
   valid dose-response relationships may be evaluated and if necessary
   protection measures could be established.}},
