   weather stations sited over bare soil have consistently higher
   degree-day accumulations. Therefore, especially in and environments,
   phenology models based on temperature collected over bare soil are not
   transferable to those based on temperature recorded over irrigated
   grass. At a minimum. all degree-day-based phenology models reported in
